# CSS Grid

CSS Grid is a two-dimensional layout system.

## Enable Grid

```css
.container {
    display: grid;
}
```

## Define Columns

```css
.container {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
}
```

## Gap

```css
.container {
    gap: 20px;
}
```

## Example

```css
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
}
```

## Real-World Example

E-commerce product pages use grid layouts.

## Benefits

- Powerful layouts
- Easy responsiveness
- Better organization

## Summary

Grid simplifies complex page structures.
